author: Jason Pope
title: Receiver catches ball on defender's back
text:
Receiver catches ball on defender's back Posted: jpope@kwwl.com (KWWL) - 
A catch was made last night that many could debate is the catch of the year, so far. 
It was during the Stanford UCLA football game Thursday night. 
Stanford ran a trick play that ended with quarterback Kevin Hogan launching the ball into the end-zone for wide receiver Francis Owasu. 
Owasu catches the ball by pinning it against the defenders back. 
The play was reviewed and was ruled a touchdown. 
Stanford went on to beat their PAC 12 rival 56-35.
